.TH "ahci_platform_init_host" 9 "ahci_platform_init_host" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ahci_platform_init_host \- Bring up an ahci-platform host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ahci_platform_init_host
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ","
.BI "struct ahci_host_priv *hpriv "  ","
.BI "const struct ata_port_info *pi_template "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_host_template *sht "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
platform device pointer for the host
.IP "hpriv" 12
ahci-host private data for the host
.IP "pi_template" 12
template for the ata_port_info to use
.IP "sht" 12
scsi_host_template to use when registering
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function does all the usual steps needed to bring up an
ahci-platform host, note any necessary resources (ie clks, phys, etc.)
must be initialized / enabled before calling this.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success otherwise a negative error code
